<subSubSection id="8D724A333F37D114B4F52610B8676882" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" type="notes">
<paragraph id="AC1AA470327E7739DC64F947F1809CF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E14AC6A5F9E9A2CE1743AFE38FFF19B" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
One new species was described (
<bibRefCitation id="CAB8C0A1991B20D7A6E1C6A976AA095B" author="Hausmann, A" journalOrPublisher="SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="241 - 247" refId="B5535948" refString="Hausmann, A, 2009. New and interesting geometrid moths from the Cape Verde Islands (Lepidoptera: Geometridae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia 37: 241 - 247" title="New and interesting geometrid moths from the Cape Verde Islands (Lepidoptera: Geometridae)." volume="37" year="2009">Hausmann 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A20EAABD5F82202DB40D3382C25336C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
After synonymising 
<taxonomicName id="6F4C1421FB65E6A669DBF4BCAD33D221" authority="Matsumura, 1925" authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1925" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Aoshakuna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aoshakuna" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="333250BAA70E4C990FB3CFADE26ACC20" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Aoshakuna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FF6FAB1860CC3516858A14B21E64ED85" authorityName="Inoue" authorityYear="1946" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nipponogelasma" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="98A903BCDB52439AB37BB22CDE6F7D67" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nipponogelasma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7E383FF584825B109D52057F52C79903" author="Beljaev, EA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" pagination="55 - 68" refId="B5535761" refString="Beljaev, EA, 2007. Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini. Zootaxa 1584: 55 - 68" title="Taxonomic changes in the emerald moths (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Geometrinae) of East Asia, with notes on the systematics and phylogeny of Hemitheini." volume="1584" year="2007">Beljaev (2007)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="BD7B0B4C7AFC6233CB9C76961F0D9FDA" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Nipponogelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Nipponogelasma chlorissoides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chlorissoides">
<emphasis id="D83BCA87FC98666DC78963B8437FF2A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Nipponogelasma chlorissoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Prout, 1913) to 
<taxonomicName id="CF632385F147D877EF17D3DD14DB4901" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microloxia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFBD801372724CAEC4D1D91CB8E0D760" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Microloxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58446B9E7C8EAA09A3184C8BAE5A67DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">
<bibRefCitation id="541E0D037D6D7775FB51454504E702E2" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5536812" refString="Leraut, P, 2009. Moths of Europe-Volume 2: Geometrid moths. NAP Editions, Paris" title="Moths of Europe-Volume 2: Geometrid moths." year="2009">Leraut (2009)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised 
<taxonomicName id="D86C4962D4547B63171A928A58A9AC72" baseAuthorityName="Bubacek" baseAuthorityYear="1926" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Microloxia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Microloxia herbaria subsp. virideciliata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="herbaria" subSpecies="virideciliata">
<emphasis id="66CC13A7523F3CC9C7FCF932FFC11EFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">Microloxia herbaria virideciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="0F9EBBA2E05173F9E52569EBD5D087EF" genus="M." lsidName="M. h. subsp. herbaria" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="subSpecies" species="h." subSpecies="herbaria">
<emphasis id="9A9FAA32869303A19BF81274503BF483" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">M. h. herbaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="DB65AB96DF22977931344182269D24C4" originalValue="Hübner">Huebner</normalizedToken>
, 1813). 
<bibRefCitation id="8DCE239F8C97E24DF2F720DFF14553BE" author="Mueller, B" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" refId="B5536891" refString="Mueller, B, Erlacher, S, Hausmann, A, Rajaei, H, Sihvonen, P, Skou, P, 2019. Volume 6. Part 1. Subfamily Ennominae II: (Boarmiini, Gnophini, additions to previous volumes). Brill, Leiden" title="Volume 6. Part 1. Subfamily Ennominae II: (Boarmiini, Gnophini, additions to previous volumes)." year="2019">
<normalizedToken id="BCFFCB0401459FB0C4AAF0CD8632CD0A" originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
et al. (2019)
</bibRefCitation>
cited molecular and morphological evidence to justify elevating 
<taxonomicName id="AA862138431978DCEF0D4CDAE7D044AA" genus="M." lsidName="M. h. subsp. virideciliata" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190" rank="subSpecies" species="h." subSpecies="virideciliata">
<emphasis id="A9CBE268C592F3DB055E41126AD669B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="52190">M. h. virideciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
back to subspecies.
</paragraph>
